track_notes: To reach la Baisse dUgail at 1392m hight, you must drive on a forest road for at least 5 km. Then you must walk on the crest sometime not very easy to found and a bit dangerous; the slope is very hard sometimes. On summit plenty room for antenna and a very nice sight on the Mercantour summits all around.
track_title: Shortest but hardest way to summit

track_notes: Starting from La Brigue, plenty car park, you can climb Mont Bergiorin and Chaberta if you are healthy enought. the last part is a bit sloope but easy. plenty room for antenna.
This 2 summits day, is only for good walkers.
